                    <div class="col-sm-9">
                        <h5>QUESTIONS/ANSWERS ON PROFILE MANAGEMENT</h5>
                        <div class="accordion square" id="profilemanagement">
                            <div class="accordion-panel">
                                <div class="accordion-title">
                                    <a href="#" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#profilemanagement-1" aria-expanded="true">Does putting a profile photo is mandatory?</a>
                                </div><!-- accordion-title -->
                                <div id="profilemanagement-1" class="collapse show" data-parent="#profilemanagement">
                                    <div class="accordion-body">
                                        <p>
                                            No. However profiles are photo profiles are poorly seen on the platform as they do not inspire confidence
                                        </p>
                                    </div><!-- accordion-body -->
                                </div><!-- collapse -->
                            </div><!-- accordion-panel -->
                            <div class="accordion-panel">
                                <div class="accordion-title">
                                    <a href="#" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#profilemanagement-2">What are the conforming pieces of identification?</a>
                                </div><!-- accordion-title -->
                                <div id="profilemanagement-2" class="collapse" data-parent="#profilemanagement">
                                    <div class="accordion-body">
                                        <p>
                                            National ID or passport (other types of documents: Driver's license.. will not be accepted)
                                        </p>
                                    </div><!-- accordion-body -->
                                </div><!-- collapse -->
                            </div><!-- accordion-panel -->
                            <div class="accordion-panel">
                                <div class="accordion-title">
                                    <a href="#" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#profilemanagement-3">Is it mandatory to put an identity photo?</a>
                                </div><!-- accordion-title -->
                                <div id="profilemanagement-3" class="collapse" data-parent="#profilemanagement">
                                    <div class="accordion-body">
                                        <p>
                                            No. However it is strongly recommended for candidate profiles to download one in order to have the Green logo "profile verified" which is highly sought by employers especially for sensitive professions like nanny, childcare..
                                        </p>
                                    </div><!-- accordion-body -->
                                </div><!-- collapse -->
                            </div><!-- accordion-panel -->
                            <div class="accordion-panel">
                                <div class="accordion-title">
                                    <a href="#" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#profilemanagement-4">Is it possible to change your personal information (surname, first name, age or photo) before having your ID validated by an admin?</a>
                                </div><!-- accordion-title -->
                                <div id="profilemanagement-4" class="collapse" data-parent="#profilemanagement">
                                    <div class="accordion-body">
                                        <p>
                                            Yes, it is possible to change his personal info (surname First name, profile photo...) As long as the profile has not yet been validated by the admin. 
                                            This is why employers are suspicious of candidate profiles that are not verified
                                        </p>
                                    </div><!-- accordion-body -->
                                </div><!-- collapse -->
                            </div><!-- accordion-panel -->

                            <div class="accordion-panel">
                                <div class="accordion-title">
                                    <a href="#" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#profilemanagement-5">Is it possible to create a job application before having the profile verified by the admin?</a>
                                </div><!-- accordion-title -->
                                <div id="profilemanagement-5" class="collapse" data-parent="#profilemanagement">
                                    <div class="accordion-body">
                                        <p>
                                            Yes, it is possible to create a request even before the validation of the admin. However employers who will see that you do not yet have the green "profile verified" logo can be suspicious of your offer 
                                        </p>
                                    </div><!-- accordion-body -->
                                </div><!-- collapse -->
                            </div><!-- accordion-panel -->

                            <div class="accordion-panel">
                                <div class="accordion-title">
                                    <a href="#" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#profilemanagement-6">Is it possible to change his personal information (surname, first name, age or photo) after having his ID validated by an admin?</a>
                                </div><!-- accordion-title -->
                                <div id="profilemanagement-6" class="collapse" data-parent="#profilemanagement">
                                    <div class="accordion-body">
                                        <p>
                                            No. All information related to your identity (profile Photo, identity document, surname, first name and age) is no longer editable. 
                                            You will be able to update other information such as: your tel number, your email address, your place of residence
                                        </p>
                                    </div><!-- accordion-body -->
                                </div><!-- collapse -->
                            </div><!-- accordion-panel -->
                        </div><!-- accordion -->
