                    <div class="col-sm-9">
                        <h5>QUESTIONS/ANSWERS ABOUT JOB REQUEST CREATION</h5>
                        <div class="accordion square" id="jobrequest">
                            <div class="accordion-panel">
                                <div class="accordion-title">
                                    <a href="#" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#jobrequest-1">Is it possible to add images to my job application?</a>
                                </div><!-- accordion-title -->
                                <div id="jobrequest-1" class="collapse" data-parent="#jobrequest">
                                    <div class="accordion-body">
                                        <p>
                                            Yes. The number of images is limited to 3. The images are used to highlight the service you wish to offer. (Example: For an offer of hairdresser, you can put 3 examples of hairstyles that you know how to do)
                                        </p>
                                    </div><!-- accordion-body -->
                                </div><!-- collapse -->
                            </div><!-- accordion-panel -->
                            <div class="accordion-panel">
                                <div class="accordion-title">
                                    <a href="#" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#jobrequest-2">Is my application visible to employers as soon as I submit it?</a>
                                </div><!-- accordion-title -->
                                <div id="jobrequest-2" class="collapse" data-parent="#jobrequest">
                                    <div class="accordion-body">
                                        <p>
                                            No. You have to wait for an Admin to validate it before it is visible in the employer search result
                                        </p>
                                    </div><!-- accordion-body -->
                                </div><!-- collapse -->
                            </div><!-- accordion-panel -->
                            <div class="accordion-panel">
                                <div class="accordion-title">
                                    <a href="#" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#jobrequest-3">Is it possible to delete an application once I have been hired by an employer? </a>
                                </div><!-- accordion-title -->
                                <div id="jobrequest-3" class="collapse" data-parent="#jobrequest">
                                    <div class="accordion-body">
                                        <p>
                                            Yes, it is possible to delete a request at any time from your user account in your "Managing My Requests" section
                                        </p>
                                    </div><!-- accordion-body -->
                                </div><!-- collapse -->
                            </div><!-- accordion-panel -->
                            <div class="accordion-panel">
                                <div class="accordion-title">
                                    <a href="#" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#jobrequest-4">Is it possible to display only my email address and not my tel number on my application?</a>
                                </div><!-- accordion-title -->
                                <div id="jobrequest-4" class="collapse" data-parent="#jobrequest">
                                    <div class="accordion-body">
                                        <p>
                                            Yes. If you do not wish to be contacted on your own, you can make your mail appear in your created application. This is done in your "Manage my Settings" section with the "Set your contact option" option
                                        </p>
                                    </div><!-- accordion-body -->
                                </div><!-- collapse -->
                            </div><!-- accordion-panel -->


                        </div><!-- accordion -->
                    </div><!-- col -->
                </div><!-- row -->

