                        <h5>QUESTIONS/ANSWERS RELATED TO AGENCY</h5>
                        <div class="accordion square" id="agency">
                            <div class="accordion-panel">
                                <div class="accordion-title">
                                    <a href="#" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#agency-1">Who can be considered an agency profile?</a>
                                </div><!-- accordion-title -->
                                <div id="agency-1" class="collapse" data-parent="#agency">
                                    <div class="accordion-body">
                                        <p>
                                            We consider as an agency any organization of qualified people with at least one seat (address...) or a good reputation on the net and social networks.
                                            This can be: an employment agency (nanny...) A qualifying training (speciality kitchen, beautician..), Pedagogical Center (school support)....
                                        </p>
                                    </div><!-- accordion-body -->
                                </div><!-- collapse -->
                            </div><!-- accordion-panel -->
                            <div class="accordion-panel">
                                <div class="accordion-title">
                                    <a href="#" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#agency-2">Can anyone create an agency profile?</a>
                                </div><!-- accordion-title -->
                                <div id="agency-2" class="collapse" data-parent="#agency">
                                    <div class="accordion-body">
                                        <p>
                                            No. The agency profile is reserved for our partners who offer qualified profiles and who have accepted our strict conditions of checking identities and skills of the profiles proposed on the platform
                                        </p>
                                    </div><!-- accordion-body -->
                                </div><!-- collapse -->
                            </div><!-- accordion-panel -->
                            <div class="accordion-panel">
                                <div class="accordion-title">
                                    <a href="#" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#agency-3">What are the agency-specific features?</a>
                                </div><!-- accordion-title -->
                                <div id="agency-3" class="collapse" data-parent="#agency">
                                    <div class="accordion-body">
                                        <p>
                                            The agency profiles can register all their members from their user accounts. All their registered members will have the "agency" profile which is highly appreciated by employers.
                                            The agencies have the duty to check the identity documents of their members and can thus give their members the logo verified profile. However, an audit is regularly done by the admin of the platform to make sure that the agencies do not give the logo has profiles without identity documents. Agencies abusing this feature will be removed from the platform
                                        </p>
                                    </div><!-- accordion-body -->
                                </div><!-- collapse -->
                            </div><!-- accordion-panel -->
                        </div><!-- accordion -->
                    </div><!-- col -->
                </div><!-- row -->

